<HEAD>Tokyo's Population Declines for Second Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The city's population has declined for the second consecutive year, apparently because of high real estate prices in the capital. <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>'s population as of Jan. 1 was 11,718,720, down by 21,641 from a year earlier, the metropolitan government announced Tuesday. The <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Land </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> says the average land price in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> is $ 630 a square foot. In neighboring areas, the average price ranges from $ 180 to 255 a square foot.
