<FIRST>r a PM-Nielsens     04-12 0505</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Nielsens,0516</SECOND>
<HEAD>CBS Drives for Hoop, but NBC Slam-Dunks Another Week</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Last year, the <ORGANIZATION> NCAA </ORGANIZATION> championship basketball game gave <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> a rare first place for the week in the <ORGANIZATION> A.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nielsen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> television ratings. This year's game, in which <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> defeated Seton Hall by one point in overtime, was in the top 10. But it was n't enough to knock <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> out of first place, where it has been for 42 straight weeks. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> won the week that ended Sunday with a 15.4 rating. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> had a 13.0 and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> 12.5. For the season, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> has a 16.0 rating, <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> 12.9 and CBS 12.6. The week was fairly typical, except that the onset of daylight saving time seemed to affect the earlier shows since viewers tend to be less eager to plop in front of the tube when it's still light outside. Therefore, `` The Cosby Show,'' which starts off the night for <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday, found itself in second place behind <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Roseanne,'' which is broadcast an hour later on Tuesday night, even though `` Cosby'' had a bigger share of the audience `` Roseanne'' had the highest rating _ 23.3, but a 35 share. `` Cosby'' had a 22.4 rating, but a 38 share. The rating is a percentage of the nation's 9.4 million homes with television. The share is a percentage of sets actually in use. Daylight saving time also affected the news ratings, all were down somewhat. `` ABC World News Tonight'' was first with a 10.1 rating and a 20 share, slightly ahead of the `` CBS Evening News'' with a 9.9 and 20 share. `` NBC Nightly News'' had an 8.9 and 18 share. The top 10 prime-time shows last week were: `` Roseanne'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>, `` The Cosby Show'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZ