his limousine. And, since he has a habit of stopping at red lights when he's on a social or recreational call, his motorcade often produces expressions of surprise and delight from other motorists and passersby as they realize the man in the stopped car alongside them is none other than the president. Those on the street might have done a double take one day last week. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, wearing exercise clothes, took his motorcade to the <ORGANIZATION> Rayburn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Office Building, where he played racquetball in the House gym. Running late for a formal dinner at the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> emerged from the gym two hours later wearing a tuxedo.
