<BYLINE>By MOHAMMED SALAM</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Christian and Moslem forces fired artillery shells at each others' strongholds in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> and nearby mountains today, and police said the barrage killed four people and wounded 17. Motorists sped away after a shell slammed into a seaside boulevard near fish restaurants in Moslem west <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Raouche </LOCATION> district. French Ambassador <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Blanc </PERSON> told reporters a shell hit the <ORGANIZATION> French </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION> compound in the <PERSON> Christian </PERSON> <PERSON> Hazmiyeh </PERSON> suburb, causing damage but no injuries. Christian and Moslem forces accused each other of ordering gunners to target residential districts of <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>. Counting today's casualties, 184 people have died and 636 have been wounded since the latest round of fighting in the civil war began March 8 between Gen. <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON>'s mostly Christian army and an alliance of Syrian and Druse forces. Also today, a Lebanese Christian security guard at the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION> was found dead from a shot to the head, police reported. They said they are investigating the death of <PERSON> Elias </PERSON> <PERSON> Haddad </PERSON>, 24, whose body was found in a building entrance about a mile from embassy compound in northern <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Aukar </LOCATION> suburb. Lebanese guards support the embassy's Marine contingent. In <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION>, a group of right-wing <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> politicians met with Foreign Minister <PERSON> Sheik </PERSON> <PERSON> Sabah </PERSON> <PERSON> Al-Ahmad </PERSON> <PERSON> Al-Sabah </PERSON>, head of a six-member Arab League panel. The politicians, led by <ORGANIZATION> Phalange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> leader <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PE