world as well as a booming birth rate. An estimated 1 million people are added to <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>'s population every 10 -LCB- months. There is widespread poverty and housing is at a premium. <PERSON> Mubarak </PERSON>, during his visit, told American businessmen his government was making progress in cutting red tape and in curbing population growth. But he said the effort was partly offset by a decline in the death rate.
