<HEAD>Bomb Kills One, Injures 40; Criticism from Sinn Fein</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A car bomb exploded next to a police station Wednesday, killing a young Roman Catholic woman and injuring 31 civilians and nine police officers, authorities said. The hospital where the victims were taken received four warnings of a blast at the police station, but all came after the bomb exploded in a stolen van parked next to the station in the coastal town of <LOCATION> Warrenpoint </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Down </LOCATION>. Suspicion fell on the <ORGANIZATION> Irish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>. The group did not immediately claim responsibility for the attack. The outlawed <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> is fighting to unite the province, where Protestants outnumber Catholics 3-to-2, with the <LOCATION> Catholic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Republic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Gerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Adams </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION>'s legal political wing, <ORGANIZATION> Sinn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fein </ORGANIZATION>, has urged the <ORGANIZATION> IRA </ORGANIZATION> to be more careful in its attacks. On Wednesday, he said: `` We are against the killing of civilians. <ORGANIZATION> Sinn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fein </ORGANIZATION> does not condone in the strongest possible terms what happened at <LOCATION> Warrenpoint </LOCATION> this morning.'' The <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ulster </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Constabulary </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Joanne </PERSON> <PERSON> Reilly </PERSON>, 20, an office worker at a hardware store next to the police station, died in the explosion. Police said most of the injured were treated and released but that five remained hospitalized at <LOCATION> Daisy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in nearby <LOCATION> Newry </LOCATION>. The hospital received the first b