d recovered a .357 - caliber Magnum pistol and a six-inch folding knife from his <PERSON> Slawson </PERSON> was living at a motel and had been visiting the couple's home earlier in the evening, according to police `` He went back later and apparently committed the murders,'' Sgt. <PERSON> Wiley </PERSON> <PERSON> Howell </PERSON> said. After the attack, Mrs. <PERSON> Wood </PERSON>, bleeding severely, managed to crawl down a staircase and to her parents house next door to summon help. Before she was taken to a hospital, Mrs. <PERSON> Wood </PERSON>, still conscious, told her mother that `` <PERSON> Newton </PERSON> killed her husband and children and stabbed her,'' Detective <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Grossi </PERSON> said in an affidavit. A description of a car seen leaving the scene was broadcast on police radio. An officer just finishing an off-duty job at a nearby food store spotted the vehicle about 45 minutes after the killings, <PERSON> Cole </PERSON> said. `` The suspect was taken into custody without incident,'' <PERSON> Cole </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Lange </PERSON>, manager of the <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gold </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Compost </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Slawson </PERSON> came to <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> late last year and worked on a package assembly line for three weeks in February. He quit to get a job at a fish camp, he said.
