<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>At the Movies: ``Winter People''</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BOB THOMAS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Some of the most interesting films of 1988 stemmed from novels: `` Dangerous Liaisons,'' `` The Accidental Tourist,'' `` Little Dorrit,'' `` The Last Temptation of Christ,'' `` The Unbearable Lightness of Being,'' `` Pelle the Conqueror.'' While original screenplays remain the most prevalent source of films, it is heartening to see the comeback of novels. Why so? Because from `` The Birth of a Nation'' to `` Gone With the Wind'' to `` Terms of Endearment,'' novels have lent film entertainment a substance that is often lacking on a diet of scripts originated by screenwriters and homogenized by countless rewrites. `` Winter People'' is the latest evidence. Adapted by <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Sobieski </PERSON> from <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Ehle </PERSON>'s novel, the film has faults and excesses. But it also offers a certain majesty and an accurate sense of time and place _ the <LOCATION> Blue </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ridge </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mountains </LOCATION> in the Depression 1930s. <PERSON> Wayland </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Kurt </PERSON> <PERSON> Russell </PERSON> -RRB- is a watchmaker who is driving his motherless daughter -LRB- <PERSON> Amelia </PERSON> <PERSON> Burnette </PERSON> -RRB- to <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> to start a new life. When their pickup truck is wrecked in a mountain stream, they take refuge with a mysterious woman -LRB- <PERSON> Kelly </PERSON> <PERSON> McGillis </PERSON> -RRB-, who lives in a remote cabin with her fatherless baby boy. The mystery unravels. <PERSON> McGillis </PERSON> has been ostracized by her family, the <ORGANIZATION> Wrights </ORGANIZATION>, who are the leading citizens of a nearby village. The father of her child is the unruly son -LRB- <PERSON> Jeffrey </PERSON> <PERSON> Meek </PERSON> -RRB- of the lawless <ORGANIZATION> Campbell </ORGANIZATION> clan, longtime enemies of the <ORGANIZATION> Wrights </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Russell </PERSON> wins the young mother's confidence and love, and the respect of her family _ after proving his manhood on a bear hunt. When the father of <PERSON> McGillis </PERSON>' son dies mysteriously, the long-smoldering feud between the Wrights and the <ORGANIZATION> Campbells </ORGANIZATION> erupts in violence. Director <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Kotcheff </PERSON> manages to keep the complicated plot running smoothly, though at times the mountain dialect is hard to comprehend. <PERSON> Kelly </PERSON> <PERSON> McGillis </PERSON> gives understated strength to her role, and <PERSON> Kurt </PERSON> <PERSON> Russell </PERSON> has his strongest characterization to date, though the transition from milquetoast to macho man is less than smooth. <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Nolan </PERSON> and <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> <PERSON> Ryan </PERSON> are powerful as patriarchs of the two families. As the violent <ORGANIZATION> Campbell </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Jeffrey </PERSON> <PERSON> Meek </PERSON> is terrifying. The mountain scenery have been stunningly photographed by <PERSON> Francois </PERSON> <PERSON> Protat </PERSON>. `` Winter People'' was produced by <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Solo </PERSON> for <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION>. Scariness and sexual tension give it a PG-13 rating. Running time: 115 minutes.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Motion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Picture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> rating definitions: G _ General audiences. All ages admitted. PG _ Parental guidance suggested. Some material may not be suitable for children. PG-13 _ Special parental guidance strongly suggested for children under 13. Some material may be inappropriate for young children. R _ Restricted. Under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult guardian. X _ No one under 17 admitted. Some states may have higher age restrictions.
</TEXT>
