<DATELINE>LEXINGTON, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Raytheon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, the defense contractor and appliance maker, said Wednesday its earnings rose 6.6 percent in the first three months of 1989. The Lexington-based company said its revenues increased 6.4 percent as strong sales of defense electronics, major appliances and other products offset a drop in aircraft purchases by the government. Because of stock repurchases, <ORGANIZATION> Raytheon </ORGANIZATION> said its earnings per share were up 8.9 percent. <ORGANIZATION> Raytheon </ORGANIZATION> reported net income for the quarter of $ 120.8 million, or $ 1.83 per share, on sales of $ 2.07 billion. That compares with net income of $ 113.3 million, or $ 1.68 per share, on sales of $ 1.95 billion in the first quarter of 1988. Chairman <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Phillips </PERSON> said all five of the company's business sectors were profitable during the quarter Those sectors are electronics, aircraft, energy services, appliances and other products. Although aircraft sales were down, <ORGANIZATION> Raytheon </ORGANIZATION> said the sector's earnings were up as its Beech division, which makes both military and civilian planes, improved its profit margins <ORGANIZATION> Raytheon </ORGANIZATION> said its electronics sector, which accounted for 51 percent of revenues last year, was led by the Missile Systems Division, which produces Hawk, Sparrow, Sidewinder and other sophisticated missiles. The appliance sector, including Amana refrigerators, Caloric ranges and Speed Queen washers, had growth in sales but a decline in profits as competition squeezed margins, the company said. <ORGANIZATION> Raytheon </ORGANIZATION> has 76,100 employees worldwide, including 30,700 in <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION>, second only to <ORGANIZATION> Digital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Equipment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the Maynard-based computer manufacturer with 35,000 