<HEAD>T-Bills Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Yields on seven-year <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> notes rose in Wednesday's auction to the highest level in 3 -LCB- years. The average yield was 9.39 percent, up from 9.30 percent at the last auction on Jan. 11. It was the highest rate since seven-year notes averaged 9.75 percent on Oct. 30, 1985. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 9 -RRB- percent with each $ 10,000 in face value selling for $ 9,992.40. A total of $ 7.02 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling $ 18.63 billion.
