<HEAD>SmithKline, Beecham Plan To Merge Into World's Second-Largest Drug
Company</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ERICH SMITH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beckman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Beecham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> announced Wednesday they would merge and form the world's second-largest pharmaceutical company, but a Wall Street analyst warned that either firm could find itself a takeover target before the transaction is completed <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Beecham </PERSON>, who confirmed earlier this month they were negotiating on a merger, said they would exchange stock and establish a pharmaceutical and health care giant with estimated sales of $ 6.7 billion. The new company, to be named <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beecham </ORGANIZATION>, would rank second in worldwide pharmaceutical sales behind <ORGANIZATION> Merck </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, second in over-the-counter medicines behind <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and fourth in animal health. The firm will have a research and development budget of more than $ 500 million per year, <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> Wendt </PERSON> said at a news conference. `` We will have one of the best and largest research and development organizations in the world, drawing on the scientific skills and traditions of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>,'' he said. Under the merger agreement, <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> shareholders would receive five `` B'' shares of stock in the new company for each of their old shares, and <PERSON> Beecham </PERSON> shareholders would receive slightly less than one `` A'' share for each of their old shares. The new shares would have equal voting rights in the affairs of <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beecham </ORGANIZATION> but dividends paid to each `` A'' share would be about five times the dividends paid to each `` B'' share. <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> currently has some 133 million shares outstanding and <PERSON> Beecham </PERSON> has about 768 million shares outstanding. Two <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> subsidiaries, <ORGANIZATION> Allergan </ORGANIZATION>, an eye - and skin-care business, and 84 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Beckman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Instruments </ORGANIZATION>, which makes diagnostic and laboratory equipment, would be spun off to <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> shareholders, the companies said in a joint statement <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> last fall sold 16 percent of <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON> through a public stock offering. <PERSON> Beecham </PERSON> plans to sell off its cosmetics and fragrance divisions, plus other non-pharmaceutical businesses, officials said. <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> shareholders would receive a one-time cash dividend of $ 5.50 per share. They also would get about half a share of <ORGANIZATION> Allergan </ORGANIZATION> and about 0.18 shares of <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> stock for each <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> share, according to a news release. The merger would be subject to governmental approval and a vote by shareholders of both companies. <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> stock fell $ 2 in <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> composite trading Wednesday, closing at $ 62.75 a share. A financial analyst specializing in pharmaceutical companies said the merger announcement could draw new bids for either company before stockholders vote four months from now. `` To quote <PERSON> Yogi </PERSON> <PERSON> Berra </PERSON>, ` It is n't over till it's over,''' said <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Nordmann </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> PaineWebber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. `` I think that's why they attempted to announce this deal in all due haste.'' Other companies mentioned as possible suitors for <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> are <ORGANIZATION> Hoffman-La </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roche </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Nestle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> SA </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Imperial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chemical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Du </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pont </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Wendt </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> had received no other offers `` There have been no feelers, no nudges, no cloakroom conversations,'' he said when pressed on the question. But <PERSON> Normann </PERSON> said the announcement could change the situation. `` Think how short the concept of this merger has been in the public domain,'' he said. `` And its such a large deal _ $ 11 to $ 13 billion, depending on what you think about the pieces. ... `` Now, X, Y, Z, who ever that might be, knows exactly what the terms are that they have to top.'' <PERSON> Wendt </PERSON>, 55, chairman and chief executive officer of <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION>, would become chairman of <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beecham </ORGANIZATION>, and <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Bauman </PERSON>, chairman of <PERSON> Beecham </PERSON>, would become chief executive officer of the new company. The two companies executed agreements Wednesday to co-promote several products, including <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION>'s popular ulcer drug Tagamet. <PERSON> Beecham </PERSON> was granted a license to sell the drug under its own brand name. <PERSON> Beecham </PERSON>, which makes Tums antacid pills, is particulary interested in developing an over-the-counter version of Tagamet, <PERSON> Bauman </PERSON> said. `` Building on the ` Tums' franchise, an over-the-counter formulation of ` Tagamet' has the potential to become a global brand,'' he said in a statement released by <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> reported total sales of $ 4.7 billion in 1988, while <PERSON> Beecham </PERSON>'s sales exceeded $ 4 billion. The new company would be based in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> with offices in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>.
