<HEAD>Energy Prices Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Gasoline futures prices surged higher in moderate trading Wednesday, fueled by rising consumer demand. Strength in the gasoline pits helped push crude prices up, while heating oil had a weaker day. On the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, unleaded gasoline for May delivery rose 1.11 cents to 70.11 cents a gallon. Most other contract months were higher. The May contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark grade of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> crude, edged up 1 penny to close the day at $ 20.64 a barrel. June and July showed no gains or losses while other months rose between 2 cents and 10 cents a barrel. Heating oil for May delivery declined .03 cent to 53.20 cents a gallon with other contract months mixed. Analysts said world demand for gasoline is continuing strong in the wake of the Alaskan oil spill nearly three weeks ago. `` A lot of strength is coming out of <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>,'' said <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Fiedler </PERSON>, analyst with <ORGANIZATION> E.D. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> F. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Man </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Futures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> `` <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> had a mild winter and people have been driving more.'' In addition, new anti-pollution regulations in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> also are affecting demand, analysts said. Contributing to the weakness in crude prices was a weekly report by the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> showing a 500,000-barrel increase in crude inventories for the week ending April 7. Market participants had expected a sharp downturn in inventories because of the Alask